# Architecture overview

Describe the project's current architecture at the level needed to keep future features consistent.

This page should identify:

- the major system boundaries and responsibilities;
- the principal components or layers and how they relate;
- the most important data, control, or interaction flows;
- durable invariants and constraints;
- links to decisions or deeper architecture pages.

Create additional pages only when a topic needs an independently useful explanation. Suitable topics vary by project and might include a command model, protocol boundary, persistence design, plugin system, concurrency model, security boundary, deployment topology, or reconciliation loop.

Keep this page current enough that a feature reviewer can determine whether a proposed design reuses established patterns or introduces a new architectural decision.
